- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper uses user-item log data to improve music feature extraction, which can be seen as an information retrieval task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method that involves training models and transferring knowledge, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with music data and proposes a method for music feature extraction, which can be considered as a multimedia task. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves natural language processing techniques for processing user-item log data, which can be seen as a subfield of computation and language.
